Habitat. Pelagic, sublittoral, on occasion taken in abundance at the surface at night (
W.M. Tattersall 1951
).

Distribution
Siriella vulgaris
was described from Indonesia and the Philippines (
Hansen 1910
). It has a widespread distribution in coastal waters in the tropical Indo-Pacific (
W.M. Tattersall 1951
). In north-eastern Australian waters it is known from Princess Charlotte Bay (
W.M. Tattersall 1928
) and the vicinity of Low Isles (
W.M. Tattersall 1936 a
). It has also been taken in Darwin harbour in the Northern Territory (
Bacescu 1986
).
